title: Prime Minister of Ukraine - Wikipedia
snippet: The current prime minister is Yulia Svyrydenko, who was confirmed by the Verkhovna Rada on 17 July 2025. She replaced Denys Shmyhal, who had been sworn in on 4 March 2020 following the resignation of Oleksiy Honcharuk.

snippet: 18 December 2025 - 15:48 Go to all galleries · Home · President · The status and powers of the President of Ukraine, as well as the election procedure are stipulated by the Constitution of Ukraine., which defines the rights and responsibilities of the President as Head of State, the election procedure, and provides for the possibility of his/her dismissal from office and termination of his/her powers.
